{
    "id": "visualEffect",
    "name": "Visual Effect",
    "isScript": false,
    "description": "A comprehensive particle effect system using three.quarks for GPU-accelerated particle emitters. Supports event-driven triggering, parent-relative positioning, duration-based auto-stop, and multiplayer synchronization. Automatically moves VFX to scene root while tracking parent transforms. Ideal for explosions, magic effects, environmental particles, and impact visuals.",
    "documentation": "## Visual Effect\nPlay particle effects in response to game events.\n\n### Trigger Modes\n- **Start On Trigger** - Activated by a Trigger behavior\n- **Trigger on Added** - Play when object enters the game\n- **Trigger by Parent Event** - Activated by parent object events\n- **Restart on Trigger** - Restart effect on each trigger\n\n### Events\n- **Trigger Events** - Game events that start the effect\n- **Stop Events** - Game events that stop the effect\n- Supports character, enemy, game, consumable, and platform events\n- **Custom Events** - Define your own event names\n\n### Tips\n- Attach to particle emitter objects only\n- Use for hit effects, pickups, footsteps, explosions\n- Chain with Consumable events for collection feedback",
    "author": "stemstudio",
    "tags": ["motion", "vfx", "particles"],
    "main": "VisualEffectBehavior.ts",
    "version": "1.0.0",
    "dependencies": {},
    "throttleConfig": {
        "throttlePriority": "MEDIUM",
        "enableFrustumCulling": true,
        "enableDistanceThrottling": true,
        "requiresConsistentUpdates": false
    },
